# 5G NR Link-Level Simulator

A Python implementation of a 5G NR link-level simulator built from scratch against the 3GPP spec. Every class maps to a specific TS section — the goal was to understand exactly what happens inside a radio stack, not just use a library that hides it.

The simulator covers the full downlink chain: transport block generation → LDPC/Polar encoding → rate matching → QAM mapping → OFDM modulation → channel (AWGN / Rayleigh / CDL / EPA) → demodulation → channel estimation → equalisation → LLR computation → HARQ combining → decoding → BER/BLER/throughput metrics. There's also a standalone BER sweep module that validates modulation performance against analytical curves.

---

## Project structure

```
5G-NR-Link-Simulator/
├── run_sim.py               # CLI entry point, parameter sweep, JSON export
│
├── config/
│   ├── sim_config.py        # SimConfig dataclass — all simulation parameters
│   └── nr_tables.py         # 3GPP MCS / TBS / CQI lookup tables (TS 38.214)
│
├── phy/
│   ├── ofdm.py              # OFDMModulator — all 5 NR numerologies, CP guard check,
│   │                        #   DMRS injection, NRFrameStructure, slot/mini-slot map
│   ├── channel.py           # AWGNChannel, RayleighChannel, FlatRayleighChannel,
│   │                        #   EPAChannel (7-tap TS 36.104), CDLChannel (A/B/C TS 38.901)
│   │                        #   + theoretical BER functions
│   ├── channel_est.py       # LSEstimator, LMMSEEstimator (TS 38.211 §7.4)
│   ├── equaliser.py         # ZFEqualiser, MMSEEqualiser, SICEqualiser (V-BLAST)
│   ├── modulation.py        # Mapper, Demapper, LLRComputer (Max-Log-MAP)
│   └── mimo.py              # MIMOChannel (Kronecker), BeamformingMatrix (DFT codebook)
│
├── coding/
│   ├── ldpc.py              # LDPCEncoder, BPDecoder (sum-product), RateMatch
│   ├── polar.py             # PolarEncoder (CRC-6), CASCLDecoder (list=8)
│   └── harq.py              # HARQProcess, HARQManager, SoftBuffer (IR combining)
│
├── mac/
│   ├── amc.py               # LinkAdaptor (CQI→MCS), OLLAController
│   └── csi.py               # CQIComputer (EESM), PMICodebook, RISelector
│
├── sim/
│   ├── link_sim.py          # LinkSimulator — main simulation engine
│   ├── metrics.py           # BERCounter, BLERCounter, ThroughputCalc
│   └── sim_ber.py           # BER sweep engine + matplotlib plots
│
└── output/                  # Generated plots land here
    ├── ber_compare.png
    ├── frame_structure.png
    ├── cp_analysis.png
    └── mcs_comparison.png
```

