## Requirements

```
python >= 3.10
numpy  >= 1.24
scipy  >= 1.10
matplotlib >= 3.7
```

```bash
pip install numpy scipy matplotlib
```

No other dependencies.

---

## Quickstart

Clone and run with defaults (CDL-A, MCS 16, SNR 15 dB, 500 slots):

```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourname/5G-NR-Link-Simulator
cd 5G-NR-Link-Simulator
python run_sim.py
```

Single SNR point, AWGN, quiet output:

```bash
python run_sim.py --channel AWGN --snr 10 --mcs 9 --slots 200 --quiet
```

SNR sweep from 0 to 25 dB over CDL-A, save results to JSON:

```bash
python run_sim.py --sweep-snr --snr-min 0 --snr-max 25 --snr-step 5 \
                  --channel CDL-A --detector MMSE --output results.json
```

Run the BER validation suite and generate all plots:

```bash
python sim/sim_ber.py
# plots saved to output/
```

